org.eclipse.papyrus.sysml14.modelelements

Interface Viewpoint

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ViewpointCustomImpl, ViewpointImpl

    public interface Viewpoint
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject
    A representation of the model object 'Viewpoint'. A Viewpoint is a specification of the conventions and rules for constructing and using a view for the purpose of addressing a set of stakeholder concerns. The languages and methods for specifying a view may reference languages and methods in another viewpoint. They specify the elements expected to be represented in the view, and may be formally or informally defined. For example, the security viewpoint may require the security requirements, security functional and physical architecture, and security test cases.

    The following features are supported:

    • Base Class
    • Concern
    • Concern List
    • Language
    • Method
    • Presentation
    • Purpose
    • Stakeholder
    See Also:
    ModelelementsPackage.getViewpoint()
